I speak from the experience of design, branding and digital product, but I have also worked in the physical realm.

Even if we live in the world where you can find almost all the information in the world in real time, not everything is DIY-able at every moment.

Thoughts and facts 😅

Well, that’s just the problem... 
Good designs have become inconvenient and uncomfortable for a market and times of speed and immediacy, because good designs last; and if they last, they don't have to be constantly renewed (which is different from iterating them) and that sometimes this is not convenient.

The discovery and research phase rarely gets the share it deserves.

You have to reach very big and important milestones that accumulate huge budgets to be able to dedicate proper resources to them.

But there are ways to hack the system... and that is by giving value to the design process and the team that develops it. It's also important to develop an openness to being shown things you hadn't thought of before. When this happens the efficiency of the design and the design process increases and thus the outcome. 

Another important aspect is to see designers (or design technicians, as I prefer to call myself and which leaves egos out) as guides, tools or helpers with a purpose.

html.ogTitle: Nouny Clock Retires: Celebrating 1000 Days of NOC ⌐◨-◨  on Base
html.ogDescription: Today marks the 1000th consecutive episode of The Noun O' Clock LIVE Show, hosted by Zero Rights Media (previously known as The Noun Square.) Since June 13/2022, for 1000 straight days (and no misses!) we have followed the Nouns DAO daily auction and hosted a fun and casual conversational touchpoint for the community. We have also onboarded thousands of artists to nouns via our frequent art contests -- a legacy that will live on through the onchain culture club we founded last year, theyellowcollective.xyz. Over the past 3 years, we have grown a following of over 30,000 fans across X, YouTube, TikTok, Instagram, Spotify and Zora with a steady stream of engaging, educational video content about nouns and nouns-adjacent ecosystems-- a legacy that will live on through Zero Rights Media. We have commissioned Ilustradora.eth here to create this commemorative piece depicting our NOC mascot "Nouny Clock", relaxing on the beach and enjoying his well-earned retirement, as ZRM sails toward the horizon, into the unknown.Thank you Dora for your art, and thank you to everyone who has supported our show over the years. Be sure to follow @basedandyellow and @zerorightsmedia on X, and /yellow & @zerorightsmedia on Warpcast to sail away with us on our next adventures.Keep Nouns Weird ⌐◨-◨
